      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">易經 40 六五</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">易經 40 六五</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>六五：君子維有解，吉；有孚于小人。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>The fifth SIX, divided, shows (its subject), the superior man (= the ruler), executing his function of removing (whatever is injurious to the idea of the hexagram), in which case there will he good fortune, and confidence in him will be shown even by the small men.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
